{
  "texts": [
    "We generate two distinct datasets (training and validation) for the Kolmogorov flow problem with Reynolds numbers in the range [100, 500], using a spatial resolution of 128 × 128.",
    "The simulation is based on the vorticity-stream function formulation.",
    "The velocity field is obtained from the computed vorticity through the stream function, while the pressure field is derived by solving the pressure Poisson equation.",
    "We employ TorchFSM (Liu et al., 2025b) to perform GPU-accelerated flow simulations using the Fourier spectral method.",
    "The training dataset includes 32 different flow conditions sampled via a Halton sequence (Kocis and Whiten, 1997), while the validation dataset contains 16 conditions."
  ]
}